<h3>What is a cookie?</h3>
	<p>A cookie is a simple text file that is stored on your computer or mobile device by a website's server and only that server will be able to retrieve or read the contents of that cookie. It allows a website to remember things like your preferences or what's in your shopping basket. Butler JCR do not use cookies to collect personal information about you.</p>
<h3>Google Analytics</h3>
	<p>Butler JCR make use of the <a href="http://www.google.com/analytics/" target="_blank">Google Analytics</a> service to understand how you navigate around our site and help improve it.<br/>
	You can <a href="http://code.google.com/apis/analytics/docs/concepts/gaConceptsCookies.html#HowGAUsesCookies" target="_blank">view further information</a> on how Google Analytics uses cookies.<br/>
	If you wish to, you can <a href="http://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/" target="_blank">opt out of Google Analytics</a></p>
<h3>Durham University</h3>
	<p>As our site is hosted by Durham University, some of the cookies stored on your visit to Butler JCR come from them, more information can be found at <a href="http://www.dur.ac.uk/about/cookies/" target="_blank">www.dur.ac.uk/about/cookies</a></p>
<h3>Session Cookies</h3>
	<p>Session cookies allow choices and logins to be remembered whilst navigating the site:<br/>
	<b>JBJCR3</b> - used to identify your browsing session. It maintains your login. If you reject it, some parts of the site requiring a log in will not work, or will log you out unexpectedly. This cookie will automatically be deleted shortly after the end of your browsing session.<br/>
	<b>username &amp; rand</b> - if you select 'remember me', these cookies will store your Durham username and a random identifier so that the site automatically logs you in when you next visit.</p>
<h3>Further Information</h3>
	<p>Please check the 'Help' menu of your browser to learn about your cookie preferences, and how to remove cookies from your system. The website <a href="http://www.allaboutcookies.org" target="_blank">www.allaboutcookies.org</a> will provide you with further information about cookies.</p>